\sum_{n=0}^\infty n(x-9)^n
\lim_{n\to \infty} |{a_{n+1}\over a_{n}}| = \lim_{n\to \infty}|{(n+1)(x-9)^{n+1}\over n(x-9)^n}| = \lim_{n\to \infty} |(x-9){n+1\over n} = lim_{n\to \infty} |x-9| = |x-9|
|x-9| \lt 1,
\sum_{n=0}^\infty n(x-9)^n
\sum_{n=0}^\infty n(x-9)^n
|x-9|<1 \Rightarrow -1 < x-9 < 1 \Rightarrow 8<x<10
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}nx^n
|x|<1
|10-9| = 1, |8-9|= 1
